<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-326-136  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 326 136.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  April 9 1990 v36 n1804 p9(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Administration drafts bill to allow joint production.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Barrett, Joyce.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Bush Administration is working on legislation that would amendthe National Cooperative Research Act of 1984 to allow jointproduct ventures as well as joint research and development.andP;  Thebill joins several other bills aimed at amending antitrust laws toallow firms to work together at a greatly reduced risk ofantitrust action.andP;  Separate bills are pending that would permitthe formation of informal partnerships to share manufacturing,equipment, plants, employees, research and development, andmarketing and promotional programs.andP;  The Administration's billwould reduce a firm's liability to that resulting from privateantitrust suits.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Statute:   National Cooperative Research Act of 1984 (amendments).andO;Topic:     LegislationAntitrust LawsCooperative Agreement.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>